item.title: CVE-2024-2410|2024-05-03T12:58:39.449Z -- protocolbuffers -- protobuf
item.description: The JsonToBinaryStream() function is part of the protocol buffers C++ implementation and is used to parse JSON from a stream. If the input is broken up into separate chunks in a certain way, the parser will attempt to read bytes from a chunk that has already been freed.
